2-D ARRAY
It consists of rows and columns.
Syntax: int[][] arr = new int[][];
first [] - no. of rows
second [] - no. of columns
While declaring the array we have to declare no. of rows and column no. is optional
Each row will act as an individual array 
Eg:- 
import java.util.*;

class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner in = new Scanner(System.in);
        int[][] arr = new int[3][2];
        for(int i = 0;i<arr.length;i++){
            for (int j =0;j<arr[i].length;j++){
                arr[i][j] = in.nextInt();
                
            }
        }
        for(int i = 0;i<arr.length;i++){
            for (int j =0;j<arr[i].length;j++){
                System.out.print(arr[i][j]);
            }
            System.out.println();
        }
    }
}
